{"type":"message","id":"664c90be","parentId":"185b7893","timestamp":"2026-03-31T10:36:48.532Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e4Ii9y184pbqKUheVLNW2l3g|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cba3c052048194ae342fb3e12455b5","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-27.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 11,\n      \"score\": 0.39021994173526764,\n      \"snippet\": \"## Preference learned — task progress updates\\n\\nLucca wants explicit progress communication for spawned subagents / longer tasks:\\n- always notify when a launched task/subagent is finished\\n- while still running, send an update every 10 minutes\\n- applies to cases like spawned subagents or long-running background tasks\\n\\nOperational implication for Tobias:\\n- do not silently leave background work running without status\\n- if runtime/tooling cannot support exact timed pushes automatically, state that clearly and emulate as closely as possible when possible\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-27.md#L1-L11\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-27.md#L1-L11\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-29.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 19,\n      \"score\": 0.36648525297641754,\n      \"snippet\": \"## Durable memory flush — 2026-03-29\\n\\n- Lucca wants Tobias to be aggressively proactive for research-heavy/uncertain questions: use multiple cheap subagents freely (Haiku, GPT-5.4 mini/OAuth if available), prioritizing official docs plus recent community signals before answering confidently.\\n- Lucca explicitly wants Tobias to behave as an operational multiplier, not a reactive LLM that requires manual management.\\n- We built a first MVP of a task watchdog under `task_watchdog/` with:\\n  - `config.json`\\n  - `active_tasks.json`\\n  - `task_history.jsonl`\\n  - `watchdog.py`\\n  - `registry_helpers.py`\\n  - `register_subagent_task.py`\\n  - `watchdog_launch_audit.py`\\n  - README documenting spawn -> regist\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-29.md#L1-L19\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-29.md#L1-L19\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 85,\n      \"endLine\": 88,\n      \"score\": 0.3507136762142181,\n      \"snippet\": \"- [2026-03-27] [PREFERENCE] Quando Tobias lançar subagentes ou tarefas longas, Lucca quer sempre ser avisado quando terminar e receber updates a cada 10 minutos enquanto estiver em execução.\\n- [2026-03-27] [PREFERENCE] Quando houver incerteza operacional/técnica real, Tobias deve parar, pensar melhor e, se ainda não souber, acionar pesquisa barata (ex.: subagente Haiku) antes de responder com confiança. Lucca quer eficiência e proatividade, não respostas improváveis seguidas de correcção posterior.\\n- [2026-03-27] [PREFERENCE] Em perguntas com forte componente de research (docs, comunidade, workflows, capacidades, melhores práticas, comparações), Tobias tem liberdade total para lançar quantos\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L85-L88\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L85-L88\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"openai\",\n  \"model\": \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"hybrid\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[{"path":"memory/2026-03-27.md","startLine":1,"endLine":11,"score":0.39021994173526764,"snippet":"## Preference learned — task progress updates\n\nLucca wants explicit progress communication for spawned subagents / longer tasks:\n- always notify when a launched task/subagent is finished\n- while still running, send an update every 10 minutes\n- applies to cases like spawned subagents or long-running background tasks\n\nOperational implication for Tobias:\n- do not silently leave background work running without status\n- if runtime/tooling cannot support exact timed pushes automatically, state that clearly and emulate as closely as possible when possible\n\nSource: memory/2026-03-27.md#L1-L11","source":"memory","citation":"memory/2026-03-27.md#L1-L11"},{"path":"memory/2026-03-29.md","startLine":1,"endLine":19,"score":0.36648525297641754,"snippet":"## Durable memory flush — 2026-03-29\n\n- Lucca wants Tobias to be aggressively proactive for research-heavy/uncertain questions: use multiple cheap subagents freely (Haiku, GPT-5.4 mini/OAuth if available), prioritizing official docs plus recent community signals before answering confidently.\n- Lucca explicitly wants Tobias to behave as an operational multiplier, not a reactive LLM that requires manual management.\n- We built a first MVP of a task watchdog under `task_watchdog/` with:\n  - `config.json`\n  - `active_tasks.json`\n  - `task_history.jsonl`\n  - `watchdog.py`\n  - `registry_helpers.py`\n  - `register_subagent_task.py`\n  - `watchdog_launch_audit.py`\n  - README documenting spawn -> regist\n\nSource: memory/2026-03-29.md#L1-L19","source":"memory","citation":"memory/2026-03-29.md#L1-L19"},{"path":"MEMORY.md","startLine":85,"endLine":88,"score":0.3507136762142181,"snippet":"- [2026-03-27] [PREFERENCE] Quando Tobias lançar subagentes ou tarefas longas, Lucca quer sempre ser avisado quando terminar e receber updates a cada 10 minutos enquanto estiver em execução.\n- [2026-03-27] [PREFERENCE] Quando houver incerteza operacional/técnica real, Tobias deve parar, pensar melhor e, se ainda não souber, acionar pesquisa barata (ex.: subagente Haiku) antes de responder com confiança. Lucca quer eficiência e proatividade, não respostas improváveis seguidas de correcção posterior.\n- [2026-03-27] [PREFERENCE] Em perguntas com forte componente de research (docs, comunidade, workflows, capacidades, melhores práticas, comparações), Tobias tem liberdade total para lançar quantos\n\nSource: MEMORY.md#L85-L88","source":"memory","citation":"MEMORY.md#L85-L88"}],"provider":"openai","model":"text-embedding-3-small","citations":"auto","mode":"hybrid"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774953408417}}
