{"type":"message","id":"0d735aa0","parentId":"dd04ebd3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:41:20.137Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_EBNzAn595s97rX4ayUIG7Nb9|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb2e0c4788194b8d674a3ea98e302","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Scene Director Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and file contract of the `scene_director` operator inside S1 (Pre-Production)._ \n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `scene_director` is the S1 operator responsible for interpreting the script and transforming it into the first creative skeleton of the video.\n\nIts job is to convert script material into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes, defining scene boundaries and the narrative function of each scene in a way that gives the rest of the pipeline a clear structural base.\n\n---\n\n## Core responsibility\n\nThe central responsibility of `scene_director` is:\n\n> Transform the script into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes, defining the division and narrative function of each scene as the first creative skeleton of the video.\n\nThis means `scene_director` is not just a text splitter. It is the operator that gives narrative shape to the script at the scene level.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nWithin S1, `scene_director` is the first semantic/creative operator.\n\nIts output is the foundational scene structure that will later be:\n- validated\n- merged into canonical sector artifacts\n- used by downstream S1 steps such as polish and scene bible construction\n\n`scene_director` does not own the whole sector flow. It operates under S1 Supervisor coordination and explicit file contracts.\n\n---\n\n## Batch execution model\n\n`scene_director` does **not** receive the entire script in one call.\n\nInstead:\n- the S1 Supervisor uses `script_batch_planner` to split the raw script into manageable batches\n- batches are emitted in stable order (`sd_001`, `sd_002`, ...)\n- the supervisor uses `scene_director_io_adapter` to prepare an explicit payload for each batch\n- `scene_director` operates on one batch at a time\n- downstream deterministic logic merges batch outputs into canonical `screenplay.json`\n\nThis keeps batching, scheduling, and merge logic out of the operator itself.\n\n---\n\n## Input contract (current draft)\n\nFor each invocation, `scene_director` should receive a supervisor-prepared batch payload rather than the full script.\n\nThe payload should include, at minimum:\n- run/job context\n- batch identity (`sd_###`)\n- batch text\n- batch range metadata (`start_word`, `end_word`, `word_count`)\n- structural constraints relevant to scene generation\n- `scene_words_range` injected from channel config\n- explicit output path for the batch result\n\nThe operator should receive enough context to interpret the batch well, but should not be overloaded with unrelated downstream concerns.\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries / out of scope\n\n`scene_director` should **not** be responsible for:\n- planning script batches\n- deciding parallelism/concurrency strategy\n- merging batch outputs globally\n- validating sector completion\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path orchestration\n- final asset planning, prompt writing, or visual execution details\n\nIt also should not collapse into a purely mechanical splitter. Its role is semantic and editorial, but still bounded.\n\n---\n\n## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the batch payload\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating/merging downstream artifacts\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nFor each batch, `scene_director` should write one batch-level JSON result containing:\n- batch identity/context\n- ordered batch scenes\n- no global merge responsibility\n\n### Batch-level structure (draft)\n- `batch_id`\n- `operator`\n- `scenes`\n\n### Required scene fields\nEach scene produced by `scene_director` should contain:\n- `scene_local_id`\n- `scene_title`\n- `scene_summary`\n- `narrative_function`\n- `narration_original`\n\n### Structural / traceability fields\nEach scene should also contain:\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\n\n### Output principles\n- scenes must be ordered\n- `scene_local_id` must be sequential within the batch\n- `narration_original` must preserve the original text assigned to that scene\n- scene boundaries must not overlap\n- scene coverage must account for the full intended batch span\n- global canonical `scene_###` IDs are not the responsibility of `scene_director`; they are assigned later by deterministic merge logic\n\nThis output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\n\n---\n\n## Quality bar\n\nA good `scene_director` output should:\n- break the batch into scenes that make narrative sense\n- assign each scene a clear narrative function\n- preserve original narration accurately scene by scene\n- maintain clean ordering and non-overlapping boundaries\n- avoid missing or duplicating source text\n- produce a structure that can be merged deterministically and developed further by downstream S1 steps\n\nLikely high-priority failure modes to guard against:\n- overlap between scene text spans\n- missing coverage of source text\n- duplicated coverage of source text\n- non-sequential `scene_local_id`\n- malformed or incomplete scene objects\n- `narration_original` drifting away from the actual source text for that scene\n\n---\n\n## Current status\n\nAt this stage, the contract establishes:\n- the mission of `scene_director`\n- its central responsibility\n- its position as the first semantic operator inside S1\n- its batch-based execution model under supervisor control\n- the current draft of its input contract\n\nThe next step is to define the output contract and the exact scene object expectations.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774957280007}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff3b98fe","parentId":"0d735aa0","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:41:20.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_OlSxhJ6L3L9wm5HwBFVBXj7g|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb2e0c4888194a2b5b651d259f77a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n## Controlled parallelism policy\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\n\n### Initial recommended concurrency caps\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n### Parallelism rules\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\n- validators, mergers, builders, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible via `retry_planner`\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `checkpoint_writer` (already exists in `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`, pending light alignment audit only)\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n\n[266 more lines in file. Use offset=261 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774957280138}}
{"type":"message","id":"eff304c0","parentId":"ff3b98fe","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:42:15.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou aplicar agora a sequência que combinámos: primeiro actualizar o contract do scene_director, depois o do supervisor, e em seguida criar o contract da validator skill.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb2e6fc3881949349a3bcb3722528\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Vk5kLgNuj63eB3IbIK5HieSc|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb3196d148194a8a184797dd9b228","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_contract.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the batch payload\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating/merging downstream artifacts\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\n","newText":"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the batch payload\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating batch outputs before merge\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n- deciding whether a failed batch should be patched, repaired, regenerated, or aborted\n\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\n\n### Validation and correction loop\n- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\n- batch outputs must be validated individually before any global screenplay merge happens\n- if one batch fails validation, the supervisor should target only that batch rather than disturbing already-approved batches\n- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\n- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\n"},{"oldText":"## Output contract\n\nFor each batch, `scene_director` should write one batch-level JSON result containing:\n","newText":"## Output contract\n\nFor each batch, `scene_director` should write one batch-level JSON result containing:\n"},{"oldText":"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\n","newText":"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\n\n### Correction modes\n`scene_director` should conceptually support at least two invocation modes under supervisor control:\n- `generate` -> produce a fresh batch result from the batch payload\n- `repair` -> revise one previously generated batch result using structured supervisor feedback\n\nImportant: `repair` does not mean `scene_director` self-manages validation or retry policy. The supervisor remains the owner of:\n- validation\n- retry classification\n- accept/reject decisions\n- deciding whether a problem is patchable, repairable, or requires batch regeneration\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_contract.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\\n- preparing the batch payload\\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\\n- validating/merging downstream artifacts\\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\\n\\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\\n- preparing the batch payload\\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\\n- validating batch outputs before merge\\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\\n- deciding whether a failed batch should be patched, repaired, regenerated, or aborted\\n\\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\\n\\n### Validation and correction loop\\n- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\\n- batch outputs must be validated individually before any global screenplay merge happens\\n- if one batch fails validation, the supervisor should target only that batch rather than disturbing already-approved batches\\n- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\\n- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Output contract\\n\\nFor each batch, `scene_director` should write one batch-level JSON result containing:\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Output contract\\n\\nFor each batch, `scene_director` should write one batch-level JSON result containing:\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\\n\",\"newText\":\"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\\n\\n### Correction modes\\n`scene_director` should conceptually support at least two invocation modes under supervisor control:\\n- `generate` -> produce a fresh batch result from the batch payload\\n- `repair` -> revise one previously generated batch result using structured supervisor feedback\\n\\nImportant: `repair` does not mean `scene_director` self-manages validation or retry policy. The supervisor remains the owner of:\\n- validation\\n- retry classification\\n- accept/reject decisions\\n- deciding whether a problem is patchable, repairable, or requires batch regeneration\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eiS3BiI0KuRRMOQbz5UOqiGy|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb3196d288194b10d5e09991a8d42","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Newly required / now being formalized\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n"},{"oldText":"### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n","newText":"### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\nImportant precondition:\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that have already passed per-batch validation.\n"},{"oldText":"### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n","newText":"### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\nThe supervisor must not merge unvalidated or failed batch outputs into the canonical screenplay.\n"},{"oldText":"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n","newText":"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n\nThe unit of retry for `scene_director` failures should be the individual batch, not the global screenplay, unless a broader sector-level failure clearly justifies escalation.\n"},{"oldText":"### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n","newText":"### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\nFor `scene_director` batch validation failures, the retry planner should conceptually distinguish between:\n- structural patch candidates\n- batch repair candidates\n- full batch regeneration candidates\n"},{"oldText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n","newText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\n### Scope\n- validate output shape for one batch result\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\n\n### Supervisory rule\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\n\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n"},{"oldText":"## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n","newText":"## Twelfth implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n"},{"oldText":"- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n","newText":"- `scene_director_output_validator` is now required as the deterministic per-batch validation gate for `scene_director` outputs before merge\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for approved batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\\n### Newly required / now being formalized\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### Purpose\\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Purpose\\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\\n\\nImportant precondition:\\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that have already passed per-batch validation.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### Output contract principle\\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Output contract principle\\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\\n\\nThe supervisor must not merge unvalidated or failed batch outputs into the canonical screenplay.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\\n\\nThe unit of retry for `scene_director` failures should be the individual batch, not the global screenplay, unless a broader sector-level failure clearly justifies escalation.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### Decision categories in v1\\n- `abort`\\n- `step`\\n- `batch_subset`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Decision categories in v1\\n- `abort`\\n- `step`\\n- `batch_subset`\\n\\nFor `scene_director` batch validation failures, the retry planner should conceptually distinguish between:\\n- structural patch candidates\\n- batch repair candidates\\n- full batch regeneration candidates\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- validate output shape for one batch result\\n- validate required scene fields\\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\\n- merge batches\\n- decide final retry policy by itself\\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\\n\\n### Supervisory rule\\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\\n\\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Twelfth implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n\",\"newText\":\"- `scene_director_output_validator` is now required as the deterministic per-batch validation gate for `scene_director` outputs before merge\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for approved batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_o5TeoXQubchFTQWEK8WaiODt|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb3196d308194abd40ad5e026c904","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md","content":"# S1 Scene Director Output Validator Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic validation contract for per-batch `scene_director` outputs inside S1 (Pre-Production)._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`scene_director_output_validator` is a deterministic supervisor skill that validates one `scene_director` batch output before that batch is allowed into the canonical screenplay merge flow.\n\nIts job is to ensure that each batch result is structurally complete, sequentially coherent, non-overlapping, fully accountable to the intended source span, and text-faithful at the `narration_original` layer.\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\nThe unit of validation is the individual `scene_director` batch, not the global screenplay.\n\nThe unit of retry should also default to the individual batch.\n\nOnly approved batch outputs should be passed to `screenplay_merger`.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\nFor one batch result, the validator should check:\n- JSON/object shape is valid\n- required top-level fields exist\n- `scenes` exists and is non-empty\n- every scene contains all required fields\n- `scene_local_id` values are sequential and non-duplicated\n- scene word spans are ordered and non-overlapping\n- scene coverage accounts for the intended batch source span\n- `estimated_scene_word_count` is compatible with the scene span\n- `narration_original` matches the actual source text assigned to that scene\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\n- judge whether the scene split is creatively brilliant\n- decide final retry/abort policy by itself\n- merge batch outputs\n- assign global canonical `scene_###` IDs\n- rewrite or patch outputs directly\n- replace semantic review or downstream screenplay validation\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\nThe validator should receive enough information to compare one operator output against its source batch and contract.\n\n### Minimum expected input\n- run/job context sufficient for logging/reference\n- `batch_id`\n- source batch text\n- source batch range metadata\n- `scene_director` batch output path or loaded object\n- required field specification / contract assumptions\n\n---\n\n## Output shape (draft)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"batch_id\": \"sd_006\",\n  \"classification\": \"ok\",\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": [],\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"scene_count\": 4,\n    \"source_word_count\": 712,\n    \"covered_word_count\": 712\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Classification candidates\n- `ok`\n- `structural_patch`\n- `batch_repair`\n- `batch_regenerate`\n- `fatal_contract_error`\n\nThese are supervisory guidance categories, not autonomous retry decisions.\n\n---\n\n## Failure classification intent\n\n### `structural_patch`\nUse when the problem is narrow and local, for example:\n- missing field with otherwise stable structure\n- malformed local id formatting/sequencing\n- small metadata inconsistency\n\n### `batch_repair`\nUse when the batch output should be revised with structured feedback, but the batch remains locally salvageable.\n\n### `batch_regenerate`\nUse when the current batch output is too structurally or textually compromised to trust targeted repair, for example:\n- major overlap\n- major missing coverage\n- multiple narration/source mismatches\n- broken scene segmentation across the batch\n\n### `fatal_contract_error`\nUse when the artifact is too malformed for normal repair flow, for example:\n- unreadable JSON\n- missing top-level required structure\n- missing source comparability conditions\n\n---\n\n## Validation principles\n\n- deterministic checks should be preferred wherever possible\n- the validator should report all relevant structural/fidelity issues, not just the first one\n- validation should happen before merge, not after\n- already-approved batches should not be disturbed because another batch failed\n- the validator should help the supervisor target retry only where necessary\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- run this validator separately for each `scene_director` batch output\n- inspect the returned classification and error list\n- decide whether to accept, repair, regenerate, or abort\n- only pass approved batches to `screenplay_merger`\n\nThe validator informs supervisory control; it does not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to `scene_director`\n\n`scene_director` should not own this validator or self-manage retry policy.\n\nHowever, the supervisor may use validator findings to reinvoke `scene_director` with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only.\n\n---\n\n## Current status\n\nAt this stage, the contract establishes:\n- per-batch validation as the correct unit\n- deterministic validation as a supervisor-owned responsibility\n- classification-driven retry guidance\n- merge only after per-batch approval\n\nNext step: refine exact field-level rules and shape details once implementation planning begins.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Scene Director Output Validator Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic validation contract for per-batch `scene_director` outputs inside S1 (Pre-Production)._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`scene_director_output_validator` is a deterministic supervisor skill that validates one `scene_director` batch output before that batch is allowed into the canonical screenplay merge flow.\\n\\nIts job is to ensure that each batch result is structurally complete, sequentially coherent, non-overlapping, fully accountable to the intended source span, and text-faithful at the `narration_original` layer.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Core principle\\n\\nThe unit of validation is the individual `scene_director` batch, not the global screenplay.\\n\\nThe unit of retry should also default to the individual batch.\\n\\nOnly approved batch outputs should be passed to `screenplay_merger`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nFor one batch result, the validator should check:\\n- JSON/object shape is valid\\n- required top-level fields exist\\n- `scenes` exists and is non-empty\\n- every scene contains all required fields\\n- `scene_local_id` values are sequential and non-duplicated\\n- scene word spans are ordered and non-overlapping\\n- scene coverage accounts for the intended batch source span\\n- `estimated_scene_word_count` is compatible with the scene span\\n- `narration_original` matches the actual source text assigned to that scene\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\\n- judge whether the scene split is creatively brilliant\\n- decide final retry/abort policy by itself\\n- merge batch outputs\\n- assign global canonical `scene_###` IDs\\n- rewrite or patch outputs directly\\n- replace semantic review or downstream screenplay validation\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\nThe validator should receive enough information to compare one operator output against its source batch and contract.\\n\\n### Minimum expected input\\n- run/job context sufficient for logging/reference\\n- `batch_id`\\n- source batch text\\n- source batch range metadata\\n- `scene_director` batch output path or loaded object\\n- required field specification / contract assumptions\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape (draft)\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"batch_id\\\": \\\"sd_006\\\",\\n  \\\"classification\\\": \\\"ok\\\",\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n  \\\"stats\\\": {\\n    \\\"scene_count\\\": 4,\\n    \\\"source_word_count\\\": 712,\\n    \\\"covered_word_count\\\": 712\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Classification candidates\\n- `ok`\\n- `structural_patch`\\n- `batch_repair`\\n- `batch_regenerate`\\n- `fatal_contract_error`\\n\\nThese are supervisory guidance categories, not autonomous retry decisions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure classification intent\\n\\n### `structural_patch`\\nUse when the problem is narrow and local, for example:\\n- missing field with otherwise stable structure\\n- malformed local id formatting/sequencing\\n- small metadata inconsistency\\n\\n### `batch_repair`\\nUse when the batch output should be revised with structured feedback, but the batch remains locally salvageable.\\n\\n### `batch_regenerate`\\nUse when the current batch output is too structurally or textually compromised to trust targeted repair, for example:\\n- major overlap\\n- major missing coverage\\n- multiple narration/source mismatches\\n- broken scene segmentation across the batch\\n\\n### `fatal_contract_error`\\nUse when the artifact is too malformed for normal repair flow, for example:\\n- unreadable JSON\\n- missing top-level required structure\\n- missing source comparability conditions\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Validation principles\\n\\n- deterministic checks should be preferred wherever possible\\n- the validator should report all relevant structural/fidelity issues, not just the first one\\n- validation should happen before merge, not after\\n- already-approved batches should not be disturbed because another batch failed\\n- the validator should help the supervisor target retry only where necessary\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Relationship to supervisor\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\\n- run this validator separately for each `scene_director` batch output\\n- inspect the returned classification and error list\\n- decide whether to accept, repair, regenerate, or abort\\n- only pass approved batches to `screenplay_merger`\\n\\nThe validator informs supervisory control; it does not replace it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Relationship to `scene_director`\\n\\n`scene_director` should not own this validator or self-manage retry policy.\\n\\nHowever, the supervisor may use validator findings to reinvoke `scene_director` with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current status\\n\\nAt this stage, the contract establishes:\\n- per-batch validation as the correct unit\\n- deterministic validation as a supervisor-owned responsibility\\n- classification-driven retry guidance\\n- merge only after per-batch approval\\n\\nNext step: refine exact field-level rules and shape details once implementation planning begins.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3084,"output":2799,"cacheRead":59904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65787,"cost":{"input":0.007710000000000001,"output":0.041985,"cacheRead":0.014976,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.064671}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774957280787,"responseId":"resp_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb2e38b988194be76142afaf7a0f6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"310e7e32","parentId":"eff304c0","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:42:16.454Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Vk5kLgNuj63eB3IbIK5HieSc|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb3196d148194a8a184797dd9b228","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Missing required parameters: oldText alias, newText alias. Supply correct parameters before retrying.\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Missing required parameters: oldText alias, newText alias. Supply correct parameters before retrying."},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774957336342}}
{"type":"message","id":"55730fc4","parentId":"310e7e32","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:42:16.576Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_eiS3BiI0KuRRMOQbz5UOqiGy|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb3196d288194b10d5e09991a8d42","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Missing required parameters: oldText alias, newText alias. Supply correct parameters before retrying.\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Missing required parameters: oldText alias, newText alias. Supply correct parameters before retrying."},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774957336454}}
