{"type":"message","id":"b2c4f171","parentId":"3e560099","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:42:48.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"As duas edições falharam por formato do tool call, mas o novo contract da validator skill já foi criado. Vou corrigir agora os dois ficheiros existentes com edições precisas.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb31d067881948be5a12de80ff867\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d8Tpx5VPXlIGmcAMrVJRlk60|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb33a76e08194a9f97a5382445d12","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_contract.md","edits":[{"oldText":"The S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the batch payload\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating/merging downstream artifacts\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\n","newText":"The S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the batch payload\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating batch outputs before merge\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n- deciding whether a failed batch should be patched, repaired, regenerated, or aborted\n\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\n\n### Validation and correction loop\n- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\n- batch outputs must be validated individually before any global screenplay merge happens\n- if one batch fails validation, the supervisor should target only that batch rather than disturbing already-approved batches\n- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\n- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\n"},{"oldText":"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\n","newText":"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\n\n### Correction modes\n`scene_director` should conceptually support at least two invocation modes under supervisor control:\n- `generate` -> produce a fresh batch result from the batch payload\n- `repair` -> revise one previously generated batch result using structured supervisor feedback\n\nImportant: `repair` does not mean `scene_director` self-manages validation or retry policy. The supervisor remains the owner of:\n- validation\n- retry classification\n- accept/reject decisions\n- deciding whether a problem is patchable, repairable, or requires batch regeneration\n"},{"oldText":"The next step is to define the output contract and the exact scene object expectations.\n","newText":"The next step is to refine the exact repair semantics and any field-level constraints needed for implementation.\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_contract.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"The S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\\n- preparing the batch payload\\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\\n- validating/merging downstream artifacts\\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\\n\\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\\n\",\"newText\":\"The S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\\n- preparing the batch payload\\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\\n- validating batch outputs before merge\\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\\n- deciding whether a failed batch should be patched, repaired, regenerated, or aborted\\n\\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\\n\\n### Validation and correction loop\\n- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\\n- batch outputs must be validated individually before any global screenplay merge happens\\n- if one batch fails validation, the supervisor should target only that batch rather than disturbing already-approved batches\\n- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\\n- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\\n\",\"newText\":\"This output should be rich enough to preserve the creative and structural value of the operator, while remaining narrower than a full `scene_bible` or downstream visual planning artifact.\\n\\n### Correction modes\\n`scene_director` should conceptually support at least two invocation modes under supervisor control:\\n- `generate` -> produce a fresh batch result from the batch payload\\n- `repair` -> revise one previously generated batch result using structured supervisor feedback\\n\\nImportant: `repair` does not mean `scene_director` self-manages validation or retry policy. The supervisor remains the owner of:\\n- validation\\n- retry classification\\n- accept/reject decisions\\n- deciding whether a problem is patchable, repairable, or requires batch regeneration\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"The next step is to define the output contract and the exact scene object expectations.\\n\",\"newText\":\"The next step is to refine the exact repair semantics and any field-level constraints needed for implementation.\\n\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_R0bZhQKyczjMqwqR8hyGGaZb|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb33a76f08194a6b0e023b16c06de","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Newly required / now being formalized\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n"},{"oldText":"### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n","newText":"### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\nImportant precondition:\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that have already passed per-batch validation.\n"},{"oldText":"### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n","newText":"### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\nThe supervisor must not merge unvalidated or failed batch outputs into the canonical screenplay.\n"},{"oldText":"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n","newText":"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n\nThe unit of retry for `scene_director` failures should be the individual batch, not the global screenplay, unless a broader sector-level failure clearly justifies escalation.\n"},{"oldText":"### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n","newText":"### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\nFor `scene_director` batch validation failures, the retry planner should conceptually distinguish between:\n- structural patch candidates\n- batch repair candidates\n- full batch regeneration candidates\n"},{"oldText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n","newText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\n### Scope\n- validate output shape for one batch result\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\n\n### Supervisory rule\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\n\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n"},{"oldText":"## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n","newText":"## Twelfth implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n"},{"oldText":"- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n","newText":"- `scene_director_output_validator` is now required as the deterministic per-batch validation gate for `scene_director` outputs before merge\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for approved batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n"}]},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\\n### Newly required / now being formalized\\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### Purpose\\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Purpose\\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\\n\\nImportant precondition:\\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that have already passed per-batch validation.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### Output contract principle\\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Output contract principle\\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\\n\\nThe supervisor must not merge unvalidated or failed batch outputs into the canonical screenplay.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\\n\\nThe unit of retry for `scene_director` failures should be the individual batch, not the global screenplay, unless a broader sector-level failure clearly justifies escalation.\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"### Decision categories in v1\\n- `abort`\\n- `step`\\n- `batch_subset`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Decision categories in v1\\n- `abort`\\n- `step`\\n- `batch_subset`\\n\\nFor `scene_director` batch validation failures, the retry planner should conceptually distinguish between:\\n- structural patch candidates\\n- batch repair candidates\\n- full batch regeneration candidates\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- validate output shape for one batch result\\n- validate required scene fields\\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\\n- merge batches\\n- decide final retry policy by itself\\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\\n\\n### Supervisory rule\\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\\n\\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Twelfth implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n\",\"newText\":\"- `scene_director_output_validator` is now required as the deterministic per-batch validation gate for `scene_director` outputs before merge\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for approved batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":263,"output":1634,"cacheRead":65664,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67561,"cost":{"input":0.0006575000000000001,"output":0.02451,"cacheRead":0.016416,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0415835}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774957337735,"responseId":"resp_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb31c6dd481948cb572eeb4f556a2"}}
