{"type":"message","id":"d51ad618","parentId":"d4fce8df","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:42:59.335Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The parallel wrapper is not accepting edits[] for this tool path, so I’ll apply the two file edits directly in separate calls now.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb33e612c8194beec5531443fa22a\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7hBPmpP6DGlu1S6V1c5LCBdh|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb33f1fe08194a42235f40356641b","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_contract.md","oldText":"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the batch payload\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating/merging downstream artifacts\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n","newText":"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the batch payload\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating batch outputs before merge\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n- deciding whether a failed batch should be patched, repaired, regenerated, or aborted\n\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\n\n### Validation and correction loop\n- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\n- batch outputs must be validated individually before any global screenplay merge happens\n- if one batch fails validation, the supervisor should target only that batch rather than disturbing already-approved batches\n- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\n- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\\n- preparing the batch payload\\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\\n- validating/merging downstream artifacts\\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\\n\\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output contract\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\\n- preparing the batch payload\\n- deciding when `scene_director` is called\\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\\n- validating batch outputs before merge\\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\\n- deciding whether a failed batch should be patched, repaired, regenerated, or aborted\\n\\n`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\\n\\n### Validation and correction loop\\n- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\\n- batch outputs must be validated individually before any global screenplay merge happens\\n- if one batch fails validation, the supervisor should target only that batch rather than disturbing already-approved batches\\n- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\\n- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output contract\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":203,"outp