{"type":"message","id":"f05f2dc7","parentId":"46fab3c5","timestamp":"2026-03-31T11:44:29.993Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_knGNjXMbdnNLOLqM7qNINMYY|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb397bc488194be06dac647de33f1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n","newText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\n### Scope\n- validate output shape for one batch result\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\n\n### Supervisory rule\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\n\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- validate output shape for one batch result\\n- validate required scene fields\\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\\n- merge batches\\n- decide final retry policy by itself\\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\\n\\n### Supervisory rule\\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\\n\\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":224,"output":275,"cacheRead":69248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69747,"cost":{"input":0.0005600000000000001,"output":0.004125,"cacheRead":0.017311999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021996999999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774957456655,"responseId":"resp_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbb395ab708194ab8e2bcba16878b5"}}
