ocs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:42:`scene_director` does **not** receive the entire script in one call.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:47:- the supervisor uses `scene_director_io_adapter` to prepare an explicit payload for each batch\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:48:- `scene_director` operates on one batch at a time\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:57:For each invocation, `scene_director` should receive a supervisor-prepared batch payload rather than the full script.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:74:`scene_director` should **not** be responsible for:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:91:- deciding when `scene_director` is called\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:97:`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:100:- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:103:- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:104:- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:110:For each batch, `scene_director` should write one batch-level JSON result containing:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:121:Each scene produced by `scene_director` should contain:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:135:For `scene_director` outputs, `start_word` and `end_word` should be **relative to the batch**, not absolute to the full script.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:148:- global canonical `scene_###` IDs are not the responsibility of `scene_director`; they are assigned later by deterministic merge logic\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:153:`scene_director` should conceptually support at least two invocation modes under supervisor control:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:157:Important: `repair` does not mean `scene_director` self-manages validation or retry policy. The supervisor remains the owner of:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:167:A good `scene_director` output should:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:188:- the mission of `scene_director`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:3:_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic validation contract for per-batch `scene_director` outputs inside S1 (Pre-Production)._\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:11:`scene_director_output_validator` is a deterministic supervisor skill that validates one `scene_director` batch output before that batch is allowed into the canonical screenplay merge flow.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:19:The unit of validation is the individual `scene_director` batch, not the global screenplay.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:44:`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:63:- `scene_director` batch output path or loaded object\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:183:- run this validator separately for each `scene_director` batch output\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:192:## Relationship to `scene_director`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:194:`scene_director` should not own this validator or self-manage retry policy.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_output_validator_contract.md:196:However, the supervisor may use validator findings to reinvoke `scene_director` with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_supervisor_contract.md:51:- S1 op