director` does **not** receive the entire script in one call.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:47:- the supervisor uses `scene_director_io_adapter` to prepare an explicit payload for each batch\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:48:- `scene_director` operates on one batch at a time\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:57:For each invocation, `scene_director` should receive a supervisor-prepared batch payload rather than the full script.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:74:`scene_director` should **not** be responsible for:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:91:- deciding when `scene_director` is called\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:97:`scene_director` is responsible for producing the batch-level scene structure output expected by the supervisor contract.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:100:- each `scene_director` batch output is a separately validatable unit\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:103:- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic skills, not to `scene_director`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_scene_director_contract.md:104:- `scene_director` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for the affected batch only\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\