{"type":"message","id":"4fa2e895","parentId":"d92271de","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:26:25.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a081d0819482bb0c7b995a13d6\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Z5g1qJAvFldQR3FTyWyhjd62|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a37f5c8194a20480e28615e361","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JpOEqUo03tQOlLXwI4Ggb30G|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a37f7881949f1a33d00550e9bd","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/runtime/s1/s1_start.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/runtime/s1/s1_start.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ZpCU0BKL5GDKY4QHlYNGK0yn|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a380d8819496b53b64f5c75ba4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/runtime/s1/scene_bible_builder.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/Desktop/content-factory/auto_content_factory/runtime/s1/scene_bible_builder.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_sp7eYHkmr6cCMcUelwJw1DFa|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a380e481948e16b9945e671d8d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/.openclaw/agents/sm_s1_pre_production/WORKFLOW.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/.openclaw/agents/sm_s1_pre_production/WORKFLOW.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_NEaltIe6jp02rcvJPRqsf83x|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a380ec8194accd1cc41d6afc31","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/User-OEM/.openclaw/agents/sm_s1_pre_production/OPERATORS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:/Users/User-OEM/.openclaw/agents/sm_s1_pre_production/OPERATORS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":148118,"output":201,"cacheRead":20992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":169311,"cost":{"input":0.37029500000000004,"output":0.003015,"cacheRead":0.005248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.378558}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774970776925,"responseId":"resp_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe79c790481949f81cd3d58a397b5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f45282e8","parentId":"4fa2e895","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:26:26.411Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Z5g1qJAvFldQR3FTyWyhjd62|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a37f5c8194a20480e28615e361","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n## Controlled parallelism policy\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\n\n### Initial recommended concurrency caps\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n### Parallelism rules\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\n- validators, mergers, builders, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible via `retry_planner`\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Newly required / now being formalized\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `checkpoint_writer` (already exists in `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`, pending light alignment audit only)\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Fifth implemented supervisor skill: `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\nImportant precondition:\n`screenplay_merger` should only receive batch outputs that have already passed per-batch validation.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n`screenplay_merger` does **not**:\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\nThe supervisor must not merge unvalidated or failed batch outputs into the canonical screenplay.\n\n## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n## Seventh implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives merged screenplay\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach polish batch payload should explicitly tell `tts_polish`:\n- which scenes belong to the batch\n- what the original narration is\n- what rules govern polish behavior\n- where to write the result\n\n## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered polish batch files\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged polish output should preserve:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\nwithout destroying the original screenplay layer.\n\n## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n\nThe unit of retry for `scene_director` failures should be the individual batch, not the global screenplay, unless a broader sector-level failure clearly justifies escalation.\n\n### Purpose\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\n\n### Scope\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\n- enforces retry limits\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\n\n### Out of scope\n`retry_planner` does **not**:\n- run retries itself\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\n- invoke operators or validators\n- write checkpoints\n\n### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\nFor `scene_director` batch validation failures, the retry planner should conceptually distinguish between:\n- structural patch candidates\n- batch repair candidates\n- full batch regeneration candidates\n\n## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate each `scene_director` batch output independently before any merge into canonical `screenplay.json` happens.\n\n### Scope\n- validate output shape for one batch result\n- validate required scene fields\n- validate `scene_local_id` ordering/sequencing\n- validate scene span ordering and non-overlap\n- validate coverage of the intended batch source span\n- validate that `narration_original` matches the source text assigned to each scene\n- classify failures for supervisor retry handling\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_output_validator` does **not**:\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- rewrite operator outputs directly\n- judge creative quality beyond deterministic structural/fidelity checks\n\n### Supervisory rule\nThe supervisor should validate each batch separately and only send approved batches into `screenplay_merger`.\n\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Purpose\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\n\n### Scope\n- aggregates scene counts\n- aggregates batch counts\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\n- exposes checkpoint list\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\n- run the sector\n- write checkpoints\n- validate semantic correctness\n- call operators or skills\n\n## Twelfth implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Purpose\nProvide the controlled parallelism layer for batchable operators so the supervisor can launch work in capped waves instead of all-at-once or fully sequentially.\n\n### Scope\n- receives operator batches\n- applies a concurrency cap\n- groups batches into execution waves\n- summarizes execution outcomes into completed / failed / pending sets\n\n### Initial supported operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n### Out of scope\n`operator_batch_scheduler` does **not**:\n- invoke OpenClaw operators by itself yet\n- decide semantic retry logic\n- merge outputs\n- validate content\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `scene_director_output_validator` is now required as the deterministic per-batch validation gate for `scene_director` outputs before merge\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for approved batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\n- `operator_batch_scheduler` is implemented as the controlled parallel scheduling layer for batchable operators\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774970786282}}
{"type":"message","id":"5915bf97","parentId":"f45282e8","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:26:26.543Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JpOEqUo03tQOlLXwI4Ggb30G|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a37f7881949f1a33d00550e9bd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"S1 Pre-Production — Entry Point / Supervisor.\n\nOrchestrates: scene_director -> screenplay_validator -> tts_polish -> polish_validator -> scene_bible_builder.\nManages retries (max 3 per step) and checkpoints.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nimport yaml\n\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_director_runner import run_scene_director, save_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.screenplay_validator import validate_screenplay\nfrom runtime.s1.tts_polish_runner import run_tts_polish, save_tts_polished\nfrom runtime.s1.polish_validator import validate_polish\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_builder import build_scene_bible, write_scene_bible\nfrom runtime.s1.scene_bible_schema_validator import validate_scene_bible_schema\nfrom runtime.s1.checkpoint_writer import write_checkpoint\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\nMAX_RETRIES = 3\n\n\ndef start_s1(\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    video_root: str | Path,\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run S1 Pre-Production: script_raw -> scene_bible.json.\n\n    Args:\n        job: Validated PM job dict.\n        video_root: Path to initialized run directory.\n        model: OpenAI model for LLM steps.\n\n    Returns:\n        Structured result with success, paths, checkpoints, next_step.\n    \"\"\"\n    video_root = Path(video_root)\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\", \"\")\n    account = job.get(\"account\", \"\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"\")\n\n    # Load channel config\n    config = _load_config(account, language)\n\n    # Read script\n    script_path = video_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt not found\", \"missing_script\")\n    script_raw = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    if not script_raw.strip():\n        return _error(job_id, \"script_raw.txt is empty\", \"empty_script\")\n\n    checkpoints_written = []\n\n    # ===== STEP 1: Scene Director =====\n    try:\n        screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_failed\")\n\n    screenplay_path = save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step1_screenplay\", \"scene_director\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(screenplay), \"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step1_screenplay.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 2: Screenplay Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        validation = validate_screenplay(script_raw, screenplay)\n\n        if validation[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            # Retry: re-run scene director\n            try:\n                screenplay = run_scene_director(script_raw, job, config, model=model)\n                save_screenplay(screenplay, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"Scene director retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"scene_director_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Screenplay validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {validation['details']}\", \"screenplay_validation_failed\")\n\n    # Save validation result\n    val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"screenplay_validation.json\"\n    val_path.write_text(json.dumps(validation, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated\", \"screenplay_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 3: TTS Polish =====\n    try:\n        polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_failed\")\n\n    polished_path = save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step3_tts_polished\", \"tts_polish\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\"],\n                     extra={\"model\": model})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 4: Polish Validator (with retries) =====\n    attempt = 0\n    for attempt in range(MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n        polish_val = validate_polish(screenplay, polished)\n\n        if polish_val[\"valid\"]:\n            break\n\n        if attempt < MAX_RETRIES:\n            try:\n                polished = run_tts_polish(screenplay, config, job, model=model)\n                save_tts_polished(polished, video_root)\n            except Exception as e:\n                return _error(job_id, f\"TTS polish retry {attempt+1} failed: {e}\", \"tts_polish_retry_failed\")\n    else:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Polish validation failed after {MAX_RETRIES} retries: {polish_val['details']}\", \"polish_validation_failed\")\n\n    polish_val_path = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\" / \"polish_validation.json\"\n    polish_val_path.write_text(json.dumps(polish_val, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step4_polish_validated\", \"polish_validator\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\"],\n                     retries=attempt, validation_passed=True)\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 5: Scene Bible Builder =====\n    bible = build_scene_bible(polished, job, screenplay)\n\n    # Schema validate\n    schema_val = validate_scene_bible_schema(bible)\n    if not schema_val[\"valid\"]:\n        return _error(job_id, f\"Scene bible schema validation failed: {schema_val['errors']}\", \"scene_bible_schema_failed\")\n\n    bible_path = write_scene_bible(bible, video_root)\n\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_step5_scene_bible\", \"scene_bible_builder\",\n                     [\"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"])})\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\")\n\n    # ===== STEP 6: S1 Complete =====\n    write_checkpoint(video_root, \"b1_complete\", \"s1_supervisor\",\n                     [\"b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n                      \"b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json\",\n                      \"scene_bible.json\"],\n                     extra={\n                         \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n                         \"screenplay_validated\": True,\n                         \"polish_validated\": True,\n                         \"scene_bible_schema_valid\": True,\n                     })\n    checkpoints_written.append(\"b1_complete.json\")\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_complete\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"b1_complete\",\n        \"screenplay_path\": screenplay_path,\n        \"tts_polished_path\": polished_path,\n        \"scene_bible_path\": bible_path,\n        \"checkpoints_written\": checkpoints_written,\n        \"scene_count\": len(bible[\"scenes\"]),\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s2_and_s3\",\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": schema_val.get(\"warnings\", []),\n    }\n\n\ndef _load_config(account: str, language: str) -> dict:\n    config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / account / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n    if not config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Channel config not found: {config_path}\")\n    with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n\n\ndef _error(job_id: str, message: str, code: str) -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"success\": False,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"s1_failed\",\n        \"current_stage\": code,\n        \"screenplay_path\": \"\",\n        \"tts_polished_path\": \"\",\n        \"scene_bible_path\": \"\",\n        \"checkpoints_written\": [],\n        \"scene_count\": 0,\n        \"next_step\": None,\n        \"errors\": [{\"code\": code, \"message\": message}],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774970786412}}
{"type":"message","id":"84cdb6fa","parentId":"5915bf97","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:26:26.675Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ZpCU0BKL5GDKY4QHlYNGK0yn|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a380d8819496b53b64f5c75ba4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Scene Bible Builder — compiles scene_bible.json from polished screenplay.\n\nCreates the living document that all downstream sectors consume.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_scene_bible(\n    polished: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: list[dict[str, Any]],\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Build the initial scene_bible.json.\n\n    Args:\n        polished: TTS-polished scenes with 'polished' text.\n        job: PM job dict for metadata.\n        screenplay: Original screenplay with structural/narrative fields from scene_director.\n\n    Returns:\n        Complete scene_bible dict ready for JSON serialization.\n    \"\"\"\n    scenes = []\n\n    for scene_pol, scene_sp in zip(polished, screenplay):\n        scene_id = scene_sp.get(\"scene_id\", scene_pol.get(\"scene_id\", f\"scene_{len(scenes)+1:03d}\"))\n\n        scene = {\n            # S1 fields (filled now)\n            \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n            \"scene_title\": scene_sp.get(\"scene_title\", \"\"),\n            \"scene_summary\": scene_sp.get(\"scene_summary\", \"\"),\n            \"narrative_function\": scene_sp.get(\"narrative_function\", \"\"),\n            \"narration\": scene_pol.get(\"polished\", scene_sp.get(\"narration_original\", \"\")),\n            \"narration_original\": scene_sp.get(\"narration_original\", \"\"),\n            \"duration_estimate\": scene_sp.get(\"estimated_scene_word_count\", None),\n            \"source_scene_local_id\": scene_sp.get(\"scene_local_id\"),\n            \"start_word\": scene_sp.get(\"start_word\"),\n            \"end_word\": scene_sp.get(\"end_word\"),\n            \"global_start_word\": scene_sp.get(\"global_start_word\"),\n            \"global_end_word\": scene_sp.get(\"global_end_word\"),\n            # S2 fields (reserved, filled by Audio sector)\n            \"audio_clip\": None,\n            \"duration_actual\": None,\n            \"word_timestamps\": None,\n            # S3/S4 fields (reserved, filled by Visual Planning / Asset Research)\n            \"entities\": [],\n            \"assets\": [],\n            # S5 fields (reserved, filled by Visual Direction)\n            \"visual_brief\": None,\n            \"visual_direction\": None,\n            \"mood\": None,\n            # S7/S8 fields (reserved, filled by Composition / Post-Production)\n            \"composition\": None,\n            # Metadata\n            \"sectors_contributed\": [\"S1\"],\n        }\n        scenes.append(scene)\n\n    bible = {\n        \"version\": \"1.0\",\n        \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\", \"\"),\n        \"account\": job.get(\"account\", \"\"),\n        \"language\": job.get(\"language\", \"\"),\n        \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\", \"\"),\n        \"created_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        \"created_by\": \"s1_scene_bible_builder\",\n        \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        \"scenes\": scenes,\n    }\n\n    return bible\n\n\ndef write_scene_bible(\n    bible: dict[str, Any],\n    video_root: Path,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Write scene_bible.json to the ROOT of the run directory.\n\n    Returns path to written file.\n    \"\"\"\n    path = Path(video_root) / \"scene_bible.json\"\n    path.write_text(\n        json.dumps(bible, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False),\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n    )\n    return str(path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774970786544}}
{"type":"message","id":"94148d21","parentId":"84cdb6fa","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:26:26.791Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_sp7eYHkmr6cCMcUelwJw1DFa|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a380e481948e16b9945e671d8d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build scene_director payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule scene_director batches with controlled parallelism\n6. Merge scene_director outputs via `screenplay_merger`\n7. Validate screenplay\n8. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n9. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n10. Build tts_polish payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n11. Schedule tts_polish batches with controlled parallelism\n12. Merge polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n13. Validate polish\n14. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n15. Build `scene_bible.json`\n16. Validate scene bible schema\n17. Write/check checkpoints\n18. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n19. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774970786675}}
{"type":"message","id":"abf2e196","parentId":"94148d21","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:26:26.917Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_NEaltIe6jp02rcvJPRqsf83x|fc_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a380ec8194accd1cc41d6afc31","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OPERATORS.md — SM-S1\n\n## scene_director\n\n### Role\nTransformar batches do script bruto em cenas estruturadas para `screenplay.json`.\n\n### Receives\n- batch payload prepared by `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_words_range`\n- batch text\n- output path contract\n\n### Returns\nBatch result containing scene objects with at least:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `visual_direction`\n- `mood`\n- `duration_estimate`\n\n### Does not do\n- TTS polish\n- scene bible building\n- sector-level retry logic\n\n---\n\n## tts_polish\n\n### Role\nTransformar batches pequenos de cenas em narração polida para TTS sem alterar significado.\n\n### Receives\n- polish batch payload prepared by `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- original scene narration\n- `tts_polish_rules`\n- output path contract\n\n### Returns\nBatch result containing, at minimum:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n- optional `changes`\n\n### Does not do\n- overwrite original screenplay\n- sector-level retry logic\n- scene bible building\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774970786791}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b84d865","parentId":"abf2e196","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:27:09.310Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Fiz a revisão sistémica inicial do S1. Vou te devolver de forma bem clara, separando:\n\n- **o que fecha bem**\n- **o que está desalinhado**\n- **o que precisa ser actualizado**\n- **como o `scene_bible` está a nascer agora**\n\n---\n\n# 1. Visão geral: o S1 já fecha como sistema?\n## Resposta curta:\n**fecha conceitualmente, mas ainda não fecha 100% documental e runtime-wise.**\n\nOu seja:\n- a arquitectura principal já está bem desenhada\n- as peças centrais já têm forma\n- mas ainda existe **drift entre contract / workflow / runtime / workspace docs**\n\nIsso é normal nesta fase, e justamente por isso esta revisão era necessária.\n\n---\n\n# 2. O que está bem fechado hoje\n\n## A. Eixo central do S1\nJá está bem definido:\n\n### supervisor\n- `sm_s1_pre_production`\n\n### operator 1\n- `op_s1_scene_director`\n\n### validator 1\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n\n### operator 2\n- `op_s1_tts_polish`\n\n### validator 2\n- `tts_polish_output_validator` (contract já definido)\n\n### reviewer auxiliar\n- `op_s1_tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\nIsto já dá um backbone bom.\n\n---\n\n## B. Lógica de batches\nTambém está bem definida:\n\n### `scene_director`\n- unidade operacional = batch de script\n\n### `tts_polish`\n- unidade operacional = batch pequeno de cenas\n- sensibilidade de análise = cena dentro do batch\n\nIsso está bom e coerente.\n\n---\n\n## C. Filosofia do supervisor\nContinua bem formulada:\n\n- supervisor = brain\n- skills = hands\n- operators = specialists\n\nE essa filosofia continua consistente com o que desenhámos.\n\n---\n\n# 3. Onde está o desalinhamento agora\n\n## A. `s1_start.py` ainda está no fluxo protótipo antigo\nEste é o maior desalinhamento runtime actual.\n\n### hoje ele ainda faz:\n- chama `run_scene_director(...)` directamente\n- valida screenplay como step único\n- chama `run_tts_polish(...)` directamente\n- valida polish como step único\n- só depois builda scene bible\n\n## O problema\nIsto **não reflecte** o workflow novo do supervisor contract, que já diz:\n\n- preflight\n- paths resolver\n- script batching\n- scene_director IO adapter\n- scheduling\n- per-batch validation\n- merge\n- polish batching\n- tts io adapter\n- per-batch validation\n- optional semantic review\n- merge\n- scene_bible\n- result summarizer\n\n### Resumo:\n`s1_start.py` ainda está muito mais próximo do **S1 prototype monolítico** do que do **S1 supervisor novo**.\n\n---\n\n## B. `sm_s1_pre_production/WORKFLOW.md` ainda está incompleto perante o que definimos depois\nEle já está melhor do que muita coisa, mas ainda não incorpora explicitamente:\n\n### faltam ali com clareza:\n- `scene_director_output_validator` antes do `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_output_validator` antes do `tts_polish_merger`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` quando houver `needs_semantic_review`\n- repair subset de cenas no loop do `tts_polish`\n\nOu seja:\no workflow está **bom como esqueleto**, mas já ficou atrás da arquitectura que refinámos depois.\n\n---\n\n## C. `sm_s1_pre_production/OPERATORS.md` está parcialmente velho\nAqui o desalinhamento é bem explícito.\n\n### `scene_director` ainda está descrito como retornando:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `visual_direction`\n- `mood`\n- `duration_estimate`\n\nMas isso já não é o contract novo.\n\n### O contract novo do `scene_director` é:\n- `scene_local_id`\n- `scene_title`\n- `scene_summary`\n- `narrative_function`\n- `narration_original`\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\n\nEntão:\n> `OPERATORS.md` do supervisor está desactualizado para `scene_director`.\n\n### `tts_polish`\nessa secção está bem mais próxima do que definimos:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n- optional `changes`\n\nMas ainda falta talvez mencionar:\n- subset repair possible\n- semantic reviewer as auxiliary reviewer\n\n---\n\n## D. `s1_supervisor_contract.md` também já ficou para trás em alguns pontos\nEle está forte, mas já precisa de uma rodada de alinhamento com o que fizemos depois.\n\n### Está faltando explicitar:\n- `tts_polish_output_validator` como skill formalizada/requerida\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer` como layer auxiliar do loop\n- repair por subset de cenas dentro do batch de `tts_polish`\n- talvez clarificar que o reviewer semântico é agent auxiliar, não skill Python\n\n---\n\n# 4. Como o `scene_bible` está a nascer agora\n\nIsto é uma parte importante e vale resumir bem.\n\n## Hoje o `scene_bible_builder.py` já está mais alinhado com o shape novo\nEle agora preserva do screenplay:\n\n- `scene_title`\n- `scene_summary`\n- `narrative_function`\n- `narration_original`\n- `scene_local_id` → preservado como `source_scene_local_id`\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `global_start_word`\n- `global_end_word`\n\nE usa do polish:\n- `polished` como `narration`\n\n---\n\n## Então o `scene_bible` agora nasce assim:\n### camada estrutural do `scene_director`\nentra como:\n- identidade da cena\n- função narrativa\n- sumário\n- origem textual\n\n### camada oral do `tts_polish`\nentra como:\n- `narration` final falável\n\n### campos que antes vinham cedo demais\nagora ficam reservados:\n- `visual_direction: None`\n- `mood: None`\n- `visual_brief: None`\n\n---\n\n## Minha leitura sobre isso\nIsso está **melhor** do que antes.\n\nPorque antes o scene bible assumia cedo demais coisas como:\n- `visual_direction`\n- `mood`\n\nque, no desenho novo, não pertencem mais ao `scene_director`.\n\nEntão hoje o `scene_bible` está mais honesto:\n- guarda o que o S1 realmente sabe\n- deixa reservado o que outros sectores ainda vão preencher\n\n---\n\n# 5. O que mais precisa ser decidido sobre `scene_bible`\nAqui eu vejo uma pergunta importante que ainda não fechámos explicitamente:\n\n## o `scene_bible` no desenho novo deve ser:\n### A. apenas a agregação progressiva do que cada sector sabe\nou\n### B. já uma peça mais “interpretada” no final do S1\n\n### Minha leitura actual\nEstamos mais perto da opção **A**:\n> um living document progressivo\n\nE eu acho isso certo.\n\nNo estado actual, o S1 deixa nele:\n- estrutura narrativa\n- narração original\n- narração TTS\n- metadados de cena\n- placeholders para o resto\n\nIsso faz sentido.\n\n---\n\n# 6. Minha síntese do estado do S1\n\n## Conceitualmente\n**bom e já bastante robusto**\n\n## Documentalmente\n**quase lá, mas com drift em docs do supervisor**\n\n## Runtime actual\n**ainda híbrido**\n- parte nova\n- parte velha/protótipo\n\n---\n\n# 7. O que eu faria agora, em ordem\n\n## Prioridade 1 — atualizar docs do supervisor\n### mexer em:\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\WORKFLOW.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\OPERATORS.md`\n\nTalvez depois também:\n- `CONTEXT.md`\n- `STATE.md`\n- `TOOLS.md`\nse necessário\n\n### objectivo\nalinhar o supervisor com:\n- `scene_director_output_validator`\n- `tts_polish_output_validator`\n- semantic reviewer\n- subset repair\n- contracts novos de output\n\n---\n\n## Prioridade 2 — atualizar `s1_supervisor_contract.md`\nPara incorporar formalmente:\n- `tts_polish_output_validator`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n- subset repair\n- revised loop\n\n---\n\n## Prioridade 3 — decidir o destino do runtime protótipo\nAqui temos que escolher quando e como vamos migrar:\n- `s1_start.py`\n\nPorque ele ainda está no mundo antigo.\n\n### Mas eu não faria isso antes de alinhar os docs do supervisor.\nPrimeiro documentação + workflow fechados.\nDepois mexer no entrypoint/runtime.\n\n---\n\n# 8. Minha recomendação imediata\nAgora eu faria:\n\n## passo seguinte\n**atualizar o workspace do `sm_s1_pre_production`**\ncomeçando por:\n1. `WORKFLOW.md`\n2. `OPERATORS.md`\n\nPorque ali está o drift mais visível e mais perigoso para confusão.\n\nSe quiser, eu posso já fazer isso agora.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7ad9e648194bcc6f75bf2902d7a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":147451,"output":1960,"cacheRead":20992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":170403,"cost":{"input":0.36862750000000005,"output":0.0294,"cacheRead":0.005248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.4032755}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774970787666,"responseId":"resp_09c2c7891525c9bd0169cbe7a6f2108194a36163b1ff8566d2"}}
